<td id="sectionheading">
4.0 Quick Installation  
</td>
</tr>

<tr>
<td>
<table border="0" cellspacing="10" cellpadding="0">

  <tr>
  <td id="sectiontext">

This section has been included for those of you who are too impatient to read
the detail documentation.

<br/><br/>

The basic steps that you follow to install the project are as follows:

<ol start="1" type="1">

<li>Have a web server setup to handle PHP4.
<br/><br/>
</li>

<li>Download a distibution from the project site.
<br/><br/>
</li>

<li>Unarchive the distribution file.
<br/><br/>
</li>

<li>Create a virtual directory with your webserver that points to the
directory created from unarchiving.
<br/><br/>
</li>

<li>Run the install script to create required directories.  The script also
sets appropriate permissions
<br/><br/>
</li>

<li>Point you browser to the index.php file located in the newly
created directory.
<br/><br/>
</li>

<li>From the Administration Interface, create a <var>Source</var> by providing  
<a href="./sourceConfiguration.html#connection">connection</a>
information for the server.  You will need to contact your MLS to complete 
this step.
<br/><br/>
</li>

<li>From the Administration Interface, create a <var>Target</var> choosing on
of the supported formats of the package.
<br/><br/>
</li>

<li>From the Administration Interface, create an <var>Extract</var> choosing 
a <var>Source</var> and a <var>Target</var>.
<br/><br/>
</li>

<li>From the main page, execute a download, specifying the <var>Extract</var>
to use.
<br/><br/>
</li>

</ol>

  </td>
